discussion_comments.comment_body:
I think we need a different name and maybe a level of two of depth.

That is, this not configuring the general "output" of Codex CLI. (To me, this name implies the "output" that I see as a user.) It is configuring something extremely specific: truncation parameters for the `shell` tool call.

This makes me wonder if should have a top level config entry named `"tools"` where keys are tool names that point to dictionaries of arbitrary properties for configuring that tool, so the JSON would look like:

```json
"tools": {
  "shell": {
    "maxBytes": 12410,
    "maxLines": 256
  }
}
```

